```
Basically you&#39;re doing the same thing, however, the example was given chaining promises before `async/await` came into play. My assumption is your code doesn&#39;t work because you can&#39;t resolve the chain with `await`. What you should do is write a function like so:

```
async function scrollDownFromElement($element, offset) {
  await browser.actions().mouseMove(element).perform();
  await browser.actions().mouseMove({x: 50, y: offset}).perform();
}
```
And then call it:
